---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<ProjectLayout
  title="ZanSDI — Zanzibar Spatial Data Infrastructure"
  year="2025–2026"
  section="GIS Project Management"
  category="GIS Project Manager · Sivan Design"
  tools={['GeoNode', 'GeoServer', 'Django', 'PostgreSQL/PostGIS', 'QGIS', 'System Design', 'Capacity Building']}
>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Background</h2>
    <div class="proj-body">
      <p>
        Zanzibar set out to build a <strong>Single Source of Truth</strong> for its spatial data — one
        national platform where government agencies can discover, share and manage geospatial
        information, and that planners, researchers and the public can use for evidence-based decisions
        across land, water, environment, infrastructure and disaster risk. ZanSDI is that platform: a
        national geoportal built for the Revolutionary Government of Zanzibar under the World
        Bank–funded <strong>BIG-Z</strong> programme, delivered by Sivan Design. As <strong>GIS Project
        Manager</strong>, I lead it end-to-end — from the original field assessment and stakeholder
        consultations, through system design and development, to the capacity-building programme that
        hands it over to its long-term owners.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Methodology</h2>
    <ul class="proj-list">
      <li>Authored the <strong>System Design and Deployment Report</strong>, defining an open-source stack — <strong>GeoNode</strong>, <strong>GeoServer</strong>, <strong>Django</strong>, <strong>PostgreSQL/PostGIS</strong>, <strong>QGIS</strong> — deployed across containerized VMs with secure access controls and a structured permissions model.</li>
      <li>Designed the platform's core data schema and mapped each agency's real workflows into concrete use-cases and integrations — from syncing business-licence records with the state payment system to a dedicated teaching-data portal for the university.</li>
      <li>Ran delivery as an <strong>agile</strong> process with iterative sprints and stakeholder demos, leading testing and <strong>User Acceptance Testing (UAT)</strong> cycles for each agency.</li>
      <li>Authored the <strong>ZanSDI Capacity Building Plan</strong> — a modular, role-based training programme with a train-the-trainer track for long-term sustainability.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Results</h2>
    <div class="proj-body">
      <p>
        ZanSDI is now live as Zanzibar's national geoportal — agencies browse, query and manage
        harmonised spatial data through it daily, and the capacity-building programme is actively
        transferring ownership to the Zanzibari team that will run it long-term.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Screenshots</h2>
    <img
      src={`${base}/maps/zansdi-landing-page.jpg`}
      alt="ZanSDI geoportal landing page with the Zanzibar Spatial Data Infrastructure banner and links to Map Portals, Data Catalogue, Dashboards & GeoStories"
      class="proj-map"
      loading="lazy"
    />
    <p class="proj-map-caption">
      The ZanSDI landing page — the public entry point to Zanzibar's geoportal, linking out to map portals, the data catalogue and dashboards/GeoStories.
    </p>
    <img
      src={`${base}/maps/zansdi-web-map.jpg`}
      alt="ZanSDI interactive web map showing colour-coded land-use zones across Zanzibar Town with a layer panel and search bar"
      class="proj-map"
      loading="lazy"
    />
    <p class="proj-map-caption">
      The GeoNode-based web-map portal — agencies and the public can browse, query and overlay the platform's harmonised datasets directly in the browser.
    </p>
    <img
      src={`${base}/maps/zansdi-data-table.jpg`}
      alt="ZanSDI attribute table view listing building parcels with ID, owner, business and tax-status fields alongside a map highlighting the selected parcels"
      class="proj-map"
      loading="lazy"
    />
    <p class="proj-map-caption">
      Linked map-and-table view of a building dataset — part of the agency workflows designed to keep records and geometry in sync.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="proj-section">
    <h2 class="proj-section-title">Project Link</h2>
    <p class="proj-body">
      ZanSDI is live as Zanzibar's national geoportal.
    </p>
    <a class="proj-external proj-external-primary" href="https://zansdi.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
      Open ZanSDI →
    </a>
  </section>

</ProjectLayout>

<style>
  :global(.proj-list) {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 10px;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li) {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: #2A2A2A;
    padding-left: 1.2em;
    position: relative;
  }
  :global(.proj-list li::before) {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #3D5E35;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .proj-external {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-top: 12px;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #3D5E35;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .proj-external:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
  .proj-external-primary {
    padding: 10px 20px;
    color: #F0EAE0;
    background: #3D5E35;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }
  .proj-external-primary:hover { background: #2E4828; text-decoration: none; }
</style>
